.TH "tpm_get_random" 9 "tpm_get_random" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tpm_get_random \- get random bytes from the TPM's RNG
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tpm_get_random
.BI "(struct tpm_chip *chip "  ","
.BI "u8 *out "  ","
.BI "size_t max "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chip" 12
a \fIstruct tpm_chip\fP instance, NULL for the default chip
.IP "out" 12
destination buffer for the random bytes
.IP "max" 12
the max number of bytes to write to \fIout\fP
.SH "RETURN"
number of random bytes read or a negative error value.
